Included page: .FitNesse.SuiteAcceptanceTests.SuiteSlimTests.SetUp (edit)

Import
fitnesse.fixtures

SetUp Plugins=fitnesse.testsystems.slim.CustomTableAliasPlugin CustomComparators=glob:fitnesse.testsystems.slim.GlobComparator

Library
page driver
echo fixture

scenario login user _ with password _ user name, password
check echo @userName Bob
check echo @password xyzzy


script
login user Bob with password xyzzy
scenario login user _ with password _ user name, password
check echo Bob Bob
check echo xyzzy xyzzy


scenario beat name with a object
check echo @name Bill
check echo @object noodle

script
beat Bill with a noodle
scenario beat name with a object
check echo Bill Bill
check echo noodle noodle


login user with password
user name password
Bob xyzzy
scenario login user _ with password _ user name, password
check echo Bob Bob
check echo xyzzy xyzzy

script
login user Bob with password xyzzy
scenario login user _ with password _ user name, password
check echo Bob Bob
check echo xyzzy xyzzy

script
login user with password; Bob xyzzy
scenario login user _ with password _ user name, password
check echo Bob Bob
check echo xyzzy xyzzy

Scenarios can be defined without a filler name between the underscores

scenario my division _ _ _ numerator, denominator, quotient
setNumerator @numerator
setDenominator @denominator
check quotient @quotient

Use the Division class from the eg library to implement the scenario
Library
eg.Division

Test the scenario with a decision table

my division
# numerator denominator quotient
any comment 10 2 5.0
scenario my division _ _ _ numerator, denominator, quotient
setNumerator 10
setDenominator 2
check quotient 5.0

You can change the order of the columns
my division
quotient # numerator denominator
5.0 any comment 10 2
scenario my division _ _ _ numerator, denominator, quotient
setNumerator 10
setDenominator 2
check quotient 5.0


Test the scenario with a script

the order of the parameters can't be changed!
script
my division 20 5 4.0
scenario my division _ _ _ numerator, denominator, quotient
setNumerator 20
setDenominator 5
check quotient 4.0
my division 6 3 2.0
scenario my division _ _ _ numerator, denominator, quotient
setNumerator 6
setDenominator 3
check quotient 2.0
my division; 35 5 7.0
scenario my division _ _ _ numerator, denominator, quotient
setNumerator 35
setDenominator 5
check quotient 7.0
